7318 // them here and only add them to the enum
7319 //printf("md->qualifiedName()=%s e->name=%s tagInfo=%p name=%s\n",
7320 // qPrint(md->qualifiedName()),qPrint(e->name),(void*)e->tagInfo(),qPrint(e->name));

7322 if (isJavaLike)
7323 {
7324 qualifiedName=substitute(qualifiedName,"::",".");

7326 if (md->qualifiedName()==qualifiedName) // enum value scope matches that of the enum

7329 if (fileName.isEmpty() && e->tagInfo())
7330 {
7331 fileName = e->tagInfo()->tagName;
7332 }

7334 fileName,e->startLine,e->startColumn,

7342 fmd->setNamespace(mnd);
7343 else if (md->getFileDef())
7344 fmd->setFileDef(md->getFileDef());
7345 fmd->setOuterScope(md->getOuterScope());

7348 fmd->setId(e->id);

7355 fmd->setMemberGroupId(e->mGrpId);
7356 fmd->setExplicitExternal(e->explicitExternal,fileName,e->startLine,e->startColumn);
7357 fmd->setRefItems(e->sli);

7362 }
7363 }

7378 // qPrint(fmd->name()),qPrint(fmd->getOuterScope()->name()));

7382 {

7385 {

7387 fmd->setEnumScope(md);
7388 }
7389 }
7390 }

7394 {

7397 {
7398 md->insertEnumField(fmd);

7401 }

7731 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(pd.get(),0,QCString(),filterTitle(pd->title()));
7732 }
7733 }
7734
7735 auto addMemberToSearchIndex = [](const MemberDef *md)
7736 {
7737 if (Doxygen::searchIndex)
7738 {
7739 Doxygen::searchIndex->setCurrentDoc(md,md->anchor(),FALSE);
7740 QCString ln=md->localName();
7741 QCString qn=md->qualifiedName();
7742 Doxygen::searchIndex->addWord(ln,TRUE);
7743 if (ln!=qn)
7744 {
7745 Doxygen::searchIndex->addWord(qn,TRUE);
7746 if (md->getClassDef())
7747 {
7748 Doxygen::searchIndex->addWord(md->getClassDef()->displayName(),TRUE);
7749 }
7750 if (md->getNamespaceDef())
7751 {
7752 Doxygen::searchIndex->addWord(md->getNamespaceDef()->displayName(),TRUE);
7753 }
7754 }
7755 }
7756 };
7757
7758 auto getScope = [](const MemberDef *md)
7759 {
7760 const Definition *scope = 0;
7761 if (md->getGroupDef()) scope = md->getGroupDef();
7762 else if (md->getClassDef()) scope = md->getClassDef();
7763 else if (md->getNamespaceDef()) scope = md->getNamespaceDef();
7764 else if (md->getFileDef()) scope = md->getFileDef();
7765 return scope;
7766 };
7767
7768 auto addMemberToIndices = [addMemberToSearchIndex,getScope](const MemberDef *md)
7769 {
7770 if (md->isLinkableInProject())
7771 {
7772 if (!(md->isEnumerate() && md->isAnonymous()))
7773 {
7774 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(getScope(md),md);
7775 addMemberToSearchIndex(md);
7776 }
7777 if (md->isEnumerate())
7778 {
7779 for (const auto &fmd : md->enumFieldList())
7780 {
7781 Doxygen::indexList->addIndexItem(getScope(fmd),fmd);
7782 addMemberToSearchIndex(fmd);
7783 }
7784 }
7785 }
7786 };
7787
7788 // for each class member name
7789 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap)
7790 {
7791 // for each member definition
7792 for (const auto &md : *mn)
7793 {
7794 addMemberToIndices(md.get());
7795 }
7796 }
7797 // for each file/namespace function name
7798 for (const auto &mn : *Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap)
7799 {
7800 // for each member definition
7801 for (const auto &md : *mn)
7802 {
7803 addMemberToIndices(md.get());
7804 }
7805 }

◆ findEndOfTemplate()

static int findEndOfTemplate ( const QCString &  s,
int  startPos 
)
static

Searches for the end of a template in prototype s starting from character position startPos. If the end was found the position of the closing > is returned, otherwise -1 is returned.

Handles exotic cases such as

Class<(id<0)>
Class<bits<<2>
Class<"<">
Class<'<'>
Class<(")<")>
MemberListContainer::Class
@ Class

Definition at line 4367 of file doxygen.cpp.

4368{
4369 // locate end of template
4370 int e=startPos;
4371 int brCount=1;
4372 int roundCount=0;
4373 int len = s.length();
4374 bool insideString=FALSE;
4375 bool insideChar=FALSE;
4376 char pc = 0;
4377 while (e<len && brCount!=0)
4378 {
4379 char c=s.at(e);
4380 switch(c)
4381 {
4382 case '<':
4383 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4384 {
4385 if (e<len-1 && s.at(e+1)=='<')
4386 e++;
4387 else if (roundCount==0)
4388 brCount++;
4389 }
4390 break;
4391 case '>':
4392 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4393 {
4394 if (e<len-1 && s.at(e+1)=='>')
4395 e++;
4396 else if (roundCount==0)
4397 brCount--;
4398 }
4399 break;
4400 case '(':
4401 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4402 roundCount++;
4403 break;
4404 case ')':
4405 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4406 roundCount--;
4407 break;
4408 case '"':
4409 if (!insideChar)
4410 {
4411 if (insideString && pc!='\\')
4412 insideString=FALSE;
4413 else
4414 insideString=TRUE;
4415 }
4416 break;
4417 case '\'':
4418 if (!insideString)
4419 {
4420 if (insideChar && pc!='\\')
4421 insideChar=FALSE;
4422 else
4423 insideChar=TRUE;
4424 }
4425 break;
4426 }
4427 pc = c;
4428 e++;
4429 }
4430 return brCount==0 ? e : -1;
4431}

)

This function tries to find a member (in a documented class/file/namespace) that corresponds to the function/variable declaration given in funcDecl.

The boolean overloaded is used to specify whether or not a standard overload documentation line should be generated.

The boolean isFunc is a hint that indicates that this is a function instead of a variable or typedef.

2776 if (j!=std::string::npos) args=sargs.substr(0,j); // extract, e.g '[10]' from '[10])'
2777 }
2778 //printf("new: type='%s' name='%s' args='%s'\n",
2779 // qPrint(type),qPrint(name),qPrint(args));
2780 }
2781 else
2782 {
2783 int i=isFuncPtr;
2784 if (i==-1 && (root->spec&Entry::Alias)==0) i=findFunctionPtr(type.str(),root->lang); // for typedefs isFuncPtr is not yet set
2785 Debug::print(Debug::Variables,0," functionPtr? %s\n",i!=-1?"yes":"no");
2786 if (i>=0) // function pointer
2787 {
2788 int ai = type.find('[',i);
2789 if (ai>i) // function pointer array
2790 {
2791 args.prepend(type.right(type.length()-ai));
2792 type=type.left(ai);
2793 }
2794 else if (type.find(')',i)!=-1) // function ptr, not variable like "int (*bla)[10]"
2795 {
2796 type=type.left(type.length()-1);
2797 args.prepend(") ");
2798 //printf("type=%s args=%s\n",qPrint(type),qPrint(args));
2799 }
2800 }
2801 }
2802
2803 QCString scope;
2804 name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(name);
2805
2806 // find the scope of this variable
2807 int index = computeQualifiedIndex(name);
2808 if (index!=-1 && root->parent()->section==Entry::GROUPDOC_SEC && root->parent()->tagInfo())
2809 // grouped members are stored with full scope
2810 {
2811 buildScopeFromQualifiedName(name.left(index+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo());
2812 scope=name.left(index);
2813 name=name.mid(index+2);
2814 }
2815 else
2816 {
2817 Entry *p = root->parent();
2818 while ((p->section & Entry::SCOPE_MASK))
2819 {
2820 QCString scopeName = p->name;
2821 if (!scopeName.isEmpty())
2822 {
2823 scope.prepend(scopeName);
2824 break;
2825 }
2826 p=p->parent();
2827 }
2828 }
2829
2830 MemberType mtype;
2831 type=type.stripWhiteSpace();
2832 ClassDefMutable *cd=0;
2833 bool isRelated=FALSE;
2834 bool isMemberOf=FALSE;
2835
2836 QCString classScope=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(scope);
2837 classScope=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(classScope,FALSE);
2838 QCString annScopePrefix=scope.left(scope.length()-classScope.length());
2839
2840 if (name.findRev("::")!=-1)
2841 {
2842 if (type=="friend class" || type=="friend struct" ||
2843 type=="friend union")
2844 {
2845 cd=getClassMutable(scope);
2846 if (cd)
2847 {
2848 addVariableToClass(root, // entry
2849 cd, // class to add member to
2850 MemberType_Friend, // type of member
2851 type, // type value as string
2852 name, // name of the member
2853 args, // arguments as string
2854 FALSE, // from Anonymous scope
2855 0, // anonymous member
2856 Protection::Public, // protection
2857 Relationship::Member // related to a class
2858 );
2859 }
2860 }
2861 return; /* skip this member, because it is a
2862 * static variable definition (always?), which will be
2863 * found in a class scope as well, but then we know the
2864 * correct protection level, so only then it will be
2865 * inserted in the correct list!
2866 */
2867 }
2868
2869 if (type=="@")
2870 mtype=MemberType_EnumValue;
2871 else if (type.startsWith("typedef "))
2872 mtype=MemberType_Typedef;
2873 else if (type.startsWith("friend "))
2874 mtype=MemberType_Friend;
2875 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Property)
2876 mtype=MemberType_Property;
2877 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Event)
2878 mtype=MemberType_Event;
2879 else if (type.find("sequence<") != -1)
2880 mtype=sliceOpt ? MemberType_Sequence : MemberType_Typedef;
2881 else if (type.find("dictionary<") != -1)
2882 mtype=sliceOpt ? MemberType_Dictionary : MemberType_Typedef;
2883 else
2884 mtype=MemberType_Variable;
2885
2886 if (!root->relates.isEmpty()) // related variable
2887 {
2888 isRelated=TRUE;
2889 isMemberOf=(root->relatesType==RelatesType::MemberOf);
2890 if (getClass(root->relates)==0 && !scope.isEmpty())
2891 scope=mergeScopes(scope,root->relates);
2892 else
2893 scope=root->relates;
2894 }
2895
2896 cd=getClassMutable(scope);
2897 if (cd==0 && classScope!=scope) cd=getClassMutable(classScope);
2898 if (cd)
2899 {
2900 MemberDef *md=0;
2901
2902 // if cd is an anonymous (=tag less) scope we insert the member
2903 // into a non-anonymous parent scope as well. This is needed to
2904 // be able to refer to it using \var or \fn
2905
2906 //int indentDepth=0;
2907 int si=scope.find('@');
2908 //int anonyScopes = 0;
2909 //bool added=FALSE;
2910
2911 bool inlineSimpleStructs = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
2912 Relationship relationship = isMemberOf ? Relationship::Foreign :
2913 isRelated ? Relationship::Related :
2914 Relationship::Member ;
2915 if (si!=-1 && !inlineSimpleStructs) // anonymous scope or type
2916 {
2917 QCString pScope;
2918 ClassDefMutable *pcd=0;
2919 pScope = scope.left(std::max(si-2,0)); // scope without tag less parts
2920 if (!pScope.isEmpty())
2921 pScope.prepend(annScopePrefix);
2922 else if (annScopePrefix.length()>2)
2923 pScope=annScopePrefix.left(annScopePrefix.length()-2);
2924 if (name.at(0)!='@')
2925 {
2926 if (!pScope.isEmpty() && (pcd=getClassMutable(pScope)))
2927 {
2928 md=addVariableToClass(root, // entry
2929 pcd, // class to add member to
2930 mtype, // member type
2931 type, // type value as string
2932 name, // member name
2933 args, // arguments as string
2934 TRUE, // from anonymous scope
2935 0, // from anonymous member
2936 root->protection,
2937 relationship
2938 );
2939 //added=TRUE;
2940 }
2941 else // anonymous scope inside namespace or file => put variable in the global scope
2942 {
2943 if (mtype==MemberType_Variable)
2944 {
2945 md=addVariableToFile(root,mtype,pScope,type,name,args,TRUE,0);
2946 }
2947 //added=TRUE;
2948 }
2949 }
2950 }
2951
2952 //printf("name='%s' scope=%s scope.right=%s\n",
2953 // qPrint(name),qPrint(scope),
2954 // qPrint(scope.right(scope.length()-si)));
2955 addVariableToClass(root, // entry
2956 cd, // class to add member to
2957 mtype, // member type
2958 type, // type value as string
2959 name, // name of the member
2960 args, // arguments as string
2961 FALSE, // from anonymous scope
2962 md, // from anonymous member
2963 root->protection,
2964 relationship
2965 );
2966 }
2967 else if (!name.isEmpty()) // global variable
2968 {
2969 //printf("Inserting member in global scope %s!\n",qPrint(scope));
2970 addVariableToFile(root,mtype,scope,type,name,args,FALSE,/*0,*/0);
2971 }
2972
2973}
2974
2975//----------------------------------------------------------------------
2976// Searches the Entry tree for typedef documentation sections.
2977// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
2978static void buildTypedefList(const Entry *root)
2979{
2980 //printf("buildVarList(%s)\n",qPrint(rootNav->name()));
2981 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
2982 root->section==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC &&
2983 root->type.find("typedef ")!=-1 // its a typedef
2984 )
2985 {
2986 addVariable(root);
2987 }
2988 for (const auto &e : root->children())
2989 if (e->section!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)
2990 buildTypedefList(e.get());
2991}
2992
2993//----------------------------------------------------------------------
2994// Searches the Entry tree for sequence documentation sections.
2995// If found they are stored in the global list.
2996static void buildSequenceList(const Entry *root)
2997{
2998 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
2999 root->section==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC &&
3000 root->type.find("sequence<")!=-1 // it's a sequence
3001 )
3002 {
3003 addVariable(root);
3004 }
3005 for (const auto &e : root->children())
3006 if (e->section!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)
3007 buildSequenceList(e.get());
3008}
3009
3010//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3011// Searches the Entry tree for dictionary documentation sections.
3012// If found they are stored in the global list.
3013static void buildDictionaryList(const Entry *root)
3014{
3015 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
3016 root->section==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC &&
3017 root->type.find("dictionary<")!=-1 // it's a dictionary
3018 )
3019 {
3020 addVariable(root);
3021 }
3022 for (const auto &e : root->children())
3023 if (e->section!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)
3024 buildDictionaryList(e.get());
3025}
3026
3027//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3028// Searches the Entry tree for Variable documentation sections.
3029// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3030
3031static void buildVarList(const Entry *root)
3032{
3033 //printf("buildVarList(%s) section=%08x\n",qPrint(rootNav->name()),rootNav->section());
3034 int isFuncPtr=-1;
3035 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
3036 (root->type.isEmpty() || g_compoundKeywords.find(root->type.str())==g_compoundKeywords.end()) &&
3037 (
3038 (root->section==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC // it's a variable
3039 ) ||
3040 (root->section==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC && // or maybe a function pointer variable
3041 (isFuncPtr=findFunctionPtr(root->type.str(),root->lang))!=-1
3042 ) ||
3043 (root->section==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC && // class variable initialized by constructor
3044 isVarWithConstructor(root)
3045 )
3046 )
3047 ) // documented variable
3048 {
3049 addVariable(root,isFuncPtr);
3050 }
3051 for (const auto &e : root->children())
3052 if (e->section!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)
3053 buildVarList(e.get());
3054}
3055
3056//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3057// Searches the Entry tree for Interface sections (UNO IDL only).
3058// If found they are stored in their service or in the global list.
3059//
3060
3061static void addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton(
3062 const Entry *root,
3063 ClassDefMutable *cd,
3064 QCString const& rname)
3065{
3066 FileDef *fd = root->fileDef();
3067 enum MemberType type = (root->section==Entry::EXPORTED_INTERFACE_SEC)
3068 ? MemberType_Interface
3069 : MemberType_Service;
3070 QCString fileName = root->fileName;
3071 if (fileName.isEmpty() && root->tagInfo())
3072 {
3073 fileName = root->tagInfo()->tagName;
3074 }
3075 std::unique_ptr<MemberDefMutable> md { createMemberDef(
3076 fileName, root->startLine, root->startColumn, root->type, rname,
3077 "", "", root->protection, root->virt, root->stat, Relationship::Member,
3078 type, ArgumentList(), root->argList, root->metaData) };
3079 md->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3080 md->setMemberClass(cd);
3081 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3082 md->setDocsForDefinition(false);
3083 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3084 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3085 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3086 md->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3087 md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3088 md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3089 md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3090 md->setBodyDef(fd);
3091 md->setFileDef(fd);
3092 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3093 QCString const def = root->type + " " + rname;
3094 md->setDefinition(def);
3095 md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3096 md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3097 md->enableReferencedByRelation(root->referencedByRelation);
3098 md->enableReferencesRelation(root->referencesRelation);
3099 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3100
3101 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3102 " Interface Member:\n"
3103 " '%s' '%s' proto=%d\n"
3104 " def='%s'\n",
3105 qPrint(root->type),
3106 qPrint(rname),
3107 root->proto,
3108 qPrint(def)
3109 );
3110
3111
3112 // add member to the class cd
3113 cd->insertMember(md.get());
3114 // also add the member as a "base" (to get nicer diagrams)
3115 // "optional" interface/service get Protected which turns into dashed line
3116 BaseInfo base(rname,
3117 (root->spec & (Entry::Optional)) ? Protection::Protected : Protection::Public, Specifier::Normal);
3118 TemplateNameMap templateNames;
3119 findClassRelation(root,cd,cd,&base,templateNames,DocumentedOnly,true) ||
3120 findClassRelation(root,cd,cd,&base,templateNames,Undocumented,true);
3121 // add file to list of used files
3122 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
3123
3124 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3125 root->markAsProcessed();
3126 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3127
3128 // add member to the global list of all members
3129 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(rname);
3130 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3131}
3132
3133static void buildInterfaceAndServiceList(const Entry *root)
3134{
3135 if (root->section==Entry::EXPORTED_INTERFACE_SEC ||
3136 root->section==Entry::INCLUDED_SERVICE_SEC)
3137 {
3138 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3139 "EXPORTED_INTERFACE_SEC:\n"
3140 " '%s' '%s'::'%s' '%s' relates='%s' relatesType='%d' file='%s' line='%d' bodyLine='%d' #tArgLists=%zu mGrpId=%d spec=%lld proto=%d docFile=%s\n",
3141 qPrint(root->type),
3142 qPrint(root->parent()->name),
3143 qPrint(root->name),
3144 qPrint(root->args),
3145 qPrint(root->relates),
3146 root->relatesType,
3147 qPrint(root->fileName),
3148 root->startLine,
3149 root->bodyLine,
3150 root->tArgLists.size(),
3151 root->mGrpId,
3152 root->spec,
3153 root->proto,
3154 qPrint(root->docFile)
3155 );
3156
3157 QCString rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3158
3159 if (!rname.isEmpty())
3160 {
3161 QCString scope = root->parent()->name;
3162 ClassDefMutable *cd = getClassMutable(scope);
3163 assert(cd);
3164 if (cd && ((ClassDef::Interface == cd->compoundType()) ||
3165 (ClassDef::Service == cd->compoundType()) ||
3166 (ClassDef::Singleton == cd->compoundType())))
3167 {
3168 addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton(root,cd,rname);
3169 }
3170 else
3171 {
3172 assert(false); // was checked by scanner.l
3173 }
3174 }
3175 else if (rname.isEmpty())
3176 {
3177 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
3178 "Illegal member name found.");
3179 }
3180 }
3181 // can only have these in IDL anyway
3182 switch (root->lang)
3183 {
3184 case SrcLangExt_Unknown: // fall through (root node always is Unknown)
3185 case SrcLangExt_IDL:
3186 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildInterfaceAndServiceList(e.get());
3187 break;
3188 default:
3189 return; // nothing to do here
3190 }
3191}
3192
3193
3194//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3195// Searches the Entry tree for Function sections.
3196// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3197
3198static void addMethodToClass(const Entry *root,ClassDefMutable *cd,
3199 const QCString &rtype,const QCString &rname,const QCString &rargs,
3200 bool isFriend,
3201 Protection protection,bool stat,Specifier virt,uint64 spec,
3202 const QCString &relates
3203 )
3204{
3205 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3206
3207 QCString type = rtype;
3208 QCString args = rargs;
3209
3210 QCString name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(rname);
3211 name.stripPrefix("::");
3212
3213 MemberType mtype;
3214 if (isFriend) mtype=MemberType_Friend;
3215 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Signal) mtype=MemberType_Signal;
3216 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Slot) mtype=MemberType_Slot;
3217 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::DCOP) mtype=MemberType_DCOP;
3218 else mtype=MemberType_Function;
3219
3220 // strip redundant template specifier for constructors
3221 int i = -1;
3222 int j = -1;
3223 if ((fd==0 || fd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Cpp) &&
3224 !name.startsWith("operator ") && // not operator
3225 (i=name.find('<'))!=-1 && // containing <
3226 (j=name.find('>'))!=-1 && // or >
3227 (j!=i+2 || name.at(i+1)!='=') // but not the C++20 spaceship operator <=>
3228 )
3229 {
3230 name=name.left(i);
3231 }
3232
3233 QCString fileName = root->fileName;
3234 if (fileName.isEmpty() && root->tagInfo())
3235 {
3236 fileName = root->tagInfo()->tagName;
3237 }
3238
3239 //printf("root->name='%s; args='%s' root->argList='%s'\n",
3240 // qPrint(root->name),qPrint(args),qPrint(argListToString(root->argList))
3241 // );
3242
3243 // adding class member
3244 Relationship relationship = relates.isEmpty() ? Relationship::Member :
3245 root->relatesType==RelatesType::MemberOf ? Relationship::Foreign :
3246 Relationship::Related ;
3247 std::unique_ptr<MemberDefMutable> md { createMemberDef(
3248 fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
3249 type,name,args,root->exception,
3250 protection,virt,
3251 stat && root->relatesType!=RelatesType::MemberOf,
3252 relationship,
3253 mtype,!root->tArgLists.empty() ? root->tArgLists.back() : ArgumentList(),
3254 root->argList, root->metaData) };
3255 md->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3256 md->setMemberClass(cd);
3257 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3258 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3259 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3260 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3261 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3262 md->setMemberSpecifiers(spec);
3263 md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3264 md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3265 md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3266 md->setRequiresClause(root->req);
3267 md->setId(root->id);
3268 md->setBodyDef(fd);
3269 md->setFileDef(fd);
3270 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3271 QCString def;
3272 QCString qualScope = cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
3273 SrcLangExt lang = cd->getLanguage();
3274 QCString scopeSeparator=getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
3275 if (scopeSeparator!="::")
3276 {
3277 qualScope = substitute(qualScope,"::",scopeSeparator);
3278 }
3279 if (lang==SrcLangExt_PHP)
3280 {
3281 // for PHP we use Class::method and Namespace\method
3282 scopeSeparator="::";
3283 }
3284// QCString optArgs = root->argList.empty() ? args : QCString();
3285 if (!relates.isEmpty() || isFriend || Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
3286 {
3287 if (!type.isEmpty())
3288 {
3289 def=type+" "+name; //+optArgs;
3290 }
3291 else
3292 {
3293 def=name; //+optArgs;
3294 }
3295 }
3296 else
3297 {
3298 if (!type.isEmpty())
3299 {
3300 def=type+" "+qualScope+scopeSeparator+name; //+optArgs;
3301 }
3302 else
3303 {
3304 def=qualScope+scopeSeparator+name; //+optArgs;
3305 }
3306 }
3307 def.stripPrefix("friend ");
3308 md->setDefinition(def);
3309 md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3310 md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3311 md->enableReferencedByRelation(root->referencedByRelation);
3312 md->enableReferencesRelation(root->referencesRelation);
3313 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3314
3315 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3316 " Func Member:\n"
3317 " '%s' '%s'::'%s' '%s' proto=%d\n"
3318 " def='%s'\n",
3319 qPrint(type),
3320 qPrint(qualScope),
3321 qPrint(rname),
3322 qPrint(args),
3323 root->proto,
3324 qPrint(def)
3325 );
3326
3327 // add member to the class cd
3328 cd->insertMember(md.get());
3329 // add file to list of used files
3330 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
3331
3332 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3333 root->markAsProcessed();
3334 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3335
3336 // add member to the global list of all members
3337 //printf("Adding member=%s class=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(cd->name()));
3338 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(name);
3339 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3340}
3341
3342//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3343
3344static void addGlobalFunction(const Entry *root,const QCString &rname,const QCString &sc)
3345{
3346 QCString scope = sc;
3347 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0," --> new function %s found!\n",qPrint(rname));
3348 //printf("New function type='%s' name='%s' args='%s' bodyLine=%d\n",
3349 // qPrint(root->type),qPrint(rname),qPrint(root->args),root->bodyLine);
3350
3351 // new global function
3352 QCString name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(rname);
3353 std::unique_ptr<MemberDefMutable> md { createMemberDef(
3354 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
3355 root->type,name,root->args,root->exception,
3356 root->protection,root->virt,root->stat,Relationship::Member,
3357 MemberType_Function,
3358 !root->tArgLists.empty() ? root->tArgLists.back() : ArgumentList(),
3359 root->argList,root->metaData) };
3360
3361 md->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3362 md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3363 md->setId(root->id);
3364 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3365 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3366 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3367 md->setPrototype(root->proto,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3368 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3369 md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3370 //md->setBody(root->body);
3371 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3372 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3373 md->setBodyDef(fd);
3374 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3375 md->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3376 md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3377 md->setRequiresClause(root->req);
3378
3379 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = 0;
3380 // see if the function is inside a namespace that was not part of
3381 // the name already (in that case nd should be non-zero already)
3382 if (root->parent()->section == Entry::NAMESPACE_SEC )
3383 {
3384 //QCString nscope=removeAnonymousScopes(root->parent()->name);
3385 QCString nscope=root->parent()->name;
3386 if (!nscope.isEmpty())
3387 {
3388 nd = getResolvedNamespaceMutable(nscope);
3389 }
3390 }
3391 else if (root->parent()->section==Entry::GROUPDOC_SEC && !scope.isEmpty())
3392 {
3393 nd = getResolvedNamespaceMutable(sc);
3394 }
3395
3396 if (!scope.isEmpty())
3397 {
3398 QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(root->lang);
3399 if (sep!="::")
3400 {
3401 scope = substitute(scope,"::",sep);
3402 }
3403 scope+=sep;
3404 }
3405
3406 if (Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES)) scope = "";
3407 QCString def;
3408 //QCString optArgs = root->argList.empty() ? QCString() : root->args;
3409 if (!root->type.isEmpty())
3410 {
3411 def=root->type+" "+scope+name; //+optArgs;
3412 }
3413 else
3414 {
3415 def=scope+name; //+optArgs;
3416 }
3417 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3418 " Global Function:\n"
3419 " '%s' '%s'::'%s' '%s' proto=%d\n"
3420 " def='%s'\n",
3421 qPrint(root->type),
3422 qPrint(scope),
3423 qPrint(rname),
3424 qPrint(root->args),
3425 root->proto,
3426 qPrint(def)
3427 );
3428 md->setDefinition(def);
3429 md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3430 md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3431 md->enableReferencedByRelation(root->referencedByRelation);
3432 md->enableReferencesRelation(root->referencesRelation);
3433 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3434
3435 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3436 if (nd && !nd->name().isEmpty() && nd->name().at(0)!='@')
3437 {
3438 // add member to namespace
3439 md->setNamespace(nd);
3440 nd->insertMember(md.get());
3441 }
3442 if (fd)
3443 {
3444 // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already
3445 // inserted it into the namespace)
3446 md->setFileDef(fd);
3447 fd->insertMember(md.get());
3448 }
3449
3450 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3451 if (root->relatesType == RelatesType::Simple) // if this is a relatesalso command,
3452 // allow find Member to pick it up
3453 {
3454 root->markAsProcessed(); // Otherwise we have finished with this entry.
3455 }
3456
3457 // add member to the list of file members
3458 //printf("Adding member=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()));
3459 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->add(name);
3460 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3461}

3465static void buildFunctionList(const Entry *root)
3466{
3467 if (root->section==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC)
3468 {
3469 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0,
3470 "FUNCTION_SEC:\n"
3471 " '%s' '%s'::'%s' '%s' relates='%s' relatesType='%d' file='%s' line='%d' bodyLine='%d' #tArgLists=%zu mGrpId=%d spec=%lld proto=%d docFile=%s\n",
3472 qPrint(root->type),
3473 qPrint(root->parent()->name),
3474 qPrint(root->name),
3475 qPrint(root->args),
3476 qPrint(root->relates),
3477 root->relatesType,
3478 qPrint(root->fileName),
3479 root->startLine,
3480 root->bodyLine,
3481 root->tArgLists.size(),
3482 root->mGrpId,
3483 root->spec,
3484 root->proto,
3485 qPrint(root->docFile)
3486 );
3487
3488 bool isFriend=root->type.find("friend ")!=-1;
3489 QCString rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3490 //printf("rname=%s\n",qPrint(rname));
3491
3492 QCString scope;
3493 int index = computeQualifiedIndex(rname);
3494 if (index!=-1 && root->parent()->section==Entry::GROUPDOC_SEC && root->parent()->tagInfo())
3495 // grouped members are stored with full scope
3496 {
3497 buildScopeFromQualifiedName(rname.left(index+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo());
3498 scope=rname.left(index);
3499 rname=rname.mid(index+2);
3500 }
3501 else
3502 {
3503 scope=root->parent()->name; //stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(root->parent->name);
3504 }
3505 if (!rname.isEmpty() && scope.find('@')==-1)
3506 {
3507 ClassDefMutable *cd=0;
3508 // check if this function's parent is a class
3509 scope=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(scope,FALSE);
3510
3511 FileDef *rfd=root->fileDef();
3512
3513 int memIndex=rname.findRev("::");
3514
3515 cd=getClassMutable(scope);
3516 if (cd && scope+"::"==rname.left(scope.length()+2)) // found A::f inside A
3517 {
3518 // strip scope from name
3519 rname=rname.right(rname.length()-root->parent()->name.length()-2);
3520 }
3521
3522 bool isMember=FALSE;
3523 if (memIndex!=-1)
3524 {
3525 int ts=rname.find('<');
3526 int te=rname.find('>');
3527 if (memIndex>0 && (ts==-1 || te==-1))
3528 {
3529 // note: the following code was replaced by inMember=TRUE to deal with a
3530 // function rname='X::foo' of class X inside a namespace also called X...
3531 // bug id 548175
3532 //nd = Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(rname.left(memIndex));
3533 //isMember = nd==0;
3534 //if (nd)
3535 //{
3536 // // strip namespace scope from name
3537 // scope=rname.left(memIndex);
3538 // rname=rname.right(rname.length()-memIndex-2);
3539 //}
3540 isMember = TRUE;
3541 }
3542 else
3543 {
3544 isMember=memIndex<ts || memIndex>te;
3545 }
3546 }
3547
3548 if (!root->parent()->name.isEmpty() &&
3549 (root->parent()->section & Entry::COMPOUND_MASK) &&
3550 cd
3551 )
3552 {
3553 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0," --> member %s of class %s!\n",
3554 qPrint(rname),qPrint(cd->name()));
3555 addMethodToClass(root,cd,root->type,rname,root->args,isFriend,
3556 root->protection,root->stat,root->virt,root->spec,root->relates);
3557 }
3558 else if (!((root->parent()->section & Entry::COMPOUND_MASK)
3559 || root->parent()->section==Entry::OBJCIMPL_SEC
3560 ) &&
3561 !isMember &&
3562 (root->relates.isEmpty() || root->relatesType==RelatesType::Duplicate) &&
3563 !root->type.startsWith("extern ") && !root->type.startsWith("typedef ")
3564 )
3565 // no member => unrelated function
3566 {
3567 /* check the uniqueness of the function name in the file.
3568 * A file could contain a function prototype and a function definition
3569 * or even multiple function prototypes.
3570 */
3571 bool found=FALSE;
3572 MemberName *mn;
3573 MemberDef *md_found=0;
3574 if ((mn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(rname)))
3575 {
3576 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0," --> function %s already found!\n",qPrint(rname));
3577 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
3578 {
3579 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
3580 if (md)
3581 {
3582 const NamespaceDef *mnd = md->getNamespaceDef();
3583 NamespaceDef *rnd = 0;
3584 //printf("root namespace=%s\n",qPrint(rootNav->parent()->name()));
3585 QCString fullScope = scope;
3586 QCString parentScope = root->parent()->name;
3587 if (!parentScope.isEmpty() && !leftScopeMatch(parentScope,scope))
3588 {
3589 if (!scope.isEmpty()) fullScope.prepend("::");
3590 fullScope.prepend(parentScope);
3591 }
3592 //printf("fullScope=%s\n",qPrint(fullScope));
3593 rnd = getResolvedNamespace(fullScope);
3594 const FileDef *mfd = md->getFileDef();
3595 QCString nsName,rnsName;
3596 if (mnd) nsName = mnd->name();
3597 if (rnd) rnsName = rnd->name();
3598 //printf("matching arguments for %s%s %s%s\n",
3599 // qPrint(md->name()),md->argsString(),qPrint(rname),qPrint(argListToString(root->argList)));
3600 const ArgumentList &mdAl = md->argumentList();
3601 const ArgumentList &mdTempl = md->templateArguments();
3602
3603 // in case of template functions, we need to check if the
3604 // functions have the same number of template parameters
3605 bool sameNumTemplateArgs = TRUE;
3606 bool matchingReturnTypes = TRUE;
3607 bool sameRequiresClause = TRUE;
3608 if (!mdTempl.empty() && !root->tArgLists.empty())
3609 {
3610 if (mdTempl.size()!=root->tArgLists.back().size())
3611 {
3612 sameNumTemplateArgs = FALSE;
3613 }
3614 if (md->typeString()!=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->type))
3615 {
3616 matchingReturnTypes = FALSE;
3617 }
3618 if (md->requiresClause()!=root->req)
3619 {
3620 sameRequiresClause = FALSE;
3621 }
3622 }
3623 else if (!mdTempl.empty() || !root->tArgLists.empty())
3624 { // if one has template parameters and the other doesn't then that also counts as a
3625 // difference
3626 sameNumTemplateArgs = FALSE;
3627 }
3628
3629 bool staticsInDifferentFiles =
3630 root->stat && md->isStatic() && root->fileName!=md->getDefFileName();
3631
3632 if (
3633 matchArguments2(md->getOuterScope(),mfd,&mdAl,
3634 rnd ? rnd : Doxygen::globalScope,rfd,&root->argList,
3635 FALSE,root->lang) &&
3636 sameNumTemplateArgs &&
3637 matchingReturnTypes &&
3638 sameRequiresClause &&
3639 !staticsInDifferentFiles
3640 )
3641 {
3642 GroupDef *gd=0;
3643 if (!root->groups.empty() && !root->groups.front().groupname.isEmpty())
3644 {
3645 gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(root->groups.front().groupname);
3646 }
3647 //printf("match!\n");
3648 //printf("mnd=%p rnd=%p nsName=%s rnsName=%s\n",mnd,rnd,qPrint(nsName),qPrint(rnsName));
3649 // see if we need to create a new member
3650 found=(mnd && rnd && nsName==rnsName) || // members are in the same namespace
3651 ((mnd==0 && rnd==0 && mfd!=0 && // no external reference and
3652 mfd->absFilePath()==root->fileName // prototype in the same file
3653 )
3654 );
3655 // otherwise, allow a duplicate global member with the same argument list
3656 if (!found && gd && gd==md->getGroupDef() && nsName==rnsName)
3657 {
3658 // member is already in the group, so we don't want to add it again.
3659 found=TRUE;
3660 }
3661
3662 //printf("combining function with prototype found=%d in namespace %s\n",
3663 // found,qPrint(nsName));
3664
3665 if (found)
3666 {
3667 // merge argument lists
3668 ArgumentList mergedArgList = root->argList;
3669 mergeArguments(const_cast<ArgumentList&>(mdAl),mergedArgList,!root->doc.isEmpty());
3670 // merge documentation
3671 if (md->documentation().isEmpty() && !root->doc.isEmpty())
3672 {
3673 if (root->proto)
3674 {
3675 //printf("setDeclArgumentList to %p\n",argList);
3676 md->moveDeclArgumentList(stringToArgumentList(root->lang,root->args));
3677 }
3678 else
3679 {
3680 md->moveArgumentList(stringToArgumentList(root->lang,root->args));
3681 }
3682 }
3683
3684 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3685 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3686 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3687 if (md->getStartBodyLine()==-1 && root->bodyLine!=-1)
3688 {
3689 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3690 md->setBodyDef(rfd);
3691 }
3692
3693 if (md->briefDescription().isEmpty() && !root->brief.isEmpty())
3694 {
3695 md->setArgsString(root->args);
3696 }
3697 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3698
3699 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3700
3701 md->enableCallGraph(md->hasCallGraph() || root->callGraph);
3702 md->enableCallerGraph(md->hasCallerGraph() || root->callerGraph);
3703 md->enableReferencedByRelation(md->hasReferencedByRelation() || root->referencedByRelation);
3704 md->enableReferencesRelation(md->hasReferencesRelation() || root->referencesRelation);
3705 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3706
3707 // merge ingroup specifiers
3708 if (md->getGroupDef()==0 && !root->groups.empty())
3709 {
3710 addMemberToGroups(root,md);
3711 }
3712 else if (md->getGroupDef()!=0 && root->groups.empty())
3713 {
3714 //printf("existing member is grouped, new member not\n");
3715 }
3716 else if (md->getGroupDef()!=0 && !root->groups.empty())
3717 {
3718 //printf("both members are grouped\n");
3719 }
3720
3721 // if md is a declaration and root is the corresponding
3722 // definition, then turn md into a definition.
3723 if (md->isPrototype() && !root->proto)
3724 {
3725 md->setDeclFile(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine(),md->getDefColumn());
3726 md->setPrototype(FALSE,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3727 }
3728 // if md is already the definition, then add the declaration info
3729 else if (!md->isPrototype() && root->proto)
3730 {
3731 md->setDeclFile(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3732 }
3733 }
3734 }
3735 }
3736 if (found)
3737 {
3738 md_found = md;
3739 break;
3740 }
3741 }
3742 }
3743 if (!found) /* global function is unique with respect to the file */
3744 {
3745 addGlobalFunction(root,rname,scope);
3746 }
3747 else
3748 {
3749 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3750 if (fd)
3751 {
3752 // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already
3753 // inserted it into the namespace)
3754 fd->insertMember(md_found);
3755 }
3756 }
3757
3758 //printf("unrelated function %d '%s' '%s' '%s'\n",
3759 // root->parent->section,qPrint(root->type),qPrint(rname),qPrint(root->args));
3760 }
3761 else
3762 {
3763 Debug::print(Debug::Functions,0," --> %s not processed!\n",qPrint(rname));
3764 }
3765 }
3766 else if (rname.isEmpty())
3767 {
3768 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
3769 "Illegal member name found."
3770 );
3771 }
3772 }
3773 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildFunctionList(e.get());
3774}

◆ processTagLessClasses()

static void processTagLessClasses ( const ClassDef *  rootCd,
const ClassDef *  cd,
ClassDefMutable *  tagParentCd,
const QCString &  prefix,
int  count 
)
static

Look through the members of class cd and its public members.

If there is a member m of a tag less struct/union, then we create a duplicate of the struct/union with the name of the member to identify it. So if cd has name S, then the tag less struct/union will get name S.m Since tag less structs can be nested we need to call this function recursively. Later on we need to patch the member types so we keep track of the hierarchy of classes we create.
